1
00:01:02,813 --> 00:01:04,393
When people finish their day

2
00:01:04,690 --> 00:01:07,240
and hurry home,

3
00:01:07,985 --> 00:01:09,405
my day starts.

4
00:01:33,721 --> 00:01:36,231
My diner is open from midnight

5
00:01:36,657 --> 00:01:38,247
to seven in the morning.

6
00:01:39,359 --> 00:01:42,239
They call it "Midnight Diner."

7
00:01:44,257 --> 00:01:45,885
PORK MISO SOUP COMBO,
BEER, SAKE, SHOCHU

8
00:01:45,885 --> 00:01:47,898
That's all I have on my menu.
PORK MISO SOUP COMBO,
BEER, SAKE, SHOCHU

9
00:01:48,129 --> 00:01:50,589
But I'll make whatever customers request,

10
00:01:51,079 --> 00:01:53,209
as long as I have the ingredients for it.

11
00:01:53,410 --> 00:01:54,950
That's my policy.

12
00:02:00,021 --> 00:02:01,271
Do I even have customers?

13
00:02:01,929 --> 00:02:03,549
More than you would expect.

14
00:02:06,401 --> 00:02:09,199
MIDNIGHT DINER:
TOKYO STORIES

15
00:02:09,200 --> 00:02:14,644
HOT POT FOR ONE

16
00:02:17,846 --> 00:02:18,886
Hot...

17
00:02:21,514 --> 00:02:22,514
Okae,

18
00:02:23,122 --> 00:02:23,952
you like it?

19
00:02:25,030 --> 00:02:26,240
Yes, I love it.

20
00:02:26,784 --> 00:02:28,744
It's a hassle to prepare at home.

21
00:02:29,259 --> 00:02:32,179
Besides, I always have a ton of
leftovers afterwards.

22
00:02:35,575 --> 00:02:37,785
Kae was Chu's classmate.

23
00:02:38,229 --> 00:02:40,878
Recently, she's been
coming here after work,

24
00:02:41,073 --> 00:02:43,243
and ordering this hot pot for one.

25
00:02:53,031 --> 00:02:54,411
Thank you for the meal.

26
00:02:55,727 --> 00:02:56,567
Well done.

27
00:02:57,428 --> 00:02:59,414
- Would you like a drink?
- Sorry.

28
00:02:59,414 --> 00:03:01,004
I must go back to work.

29
00:03:01,348 --> 00:03:02,228
Now?

30
00:03:02,828 --> 00:03:06,011
Cleaning at the no-tell motel?
Nobody leaves until the morning.

31
00:03:06,196 --> 00:03:08,536
Actually, many people do at this time.

32
00:03:09,358 --> 00:03:11,808
A young part-timer took the day off,

33
00:03:12,057 --> 00:03:13,647
so I have to cover his shift.

34
00:03:13,908 --> 00:03:15,408
Too bad.

35
00:03:16,626 --> 00:03:17,796
Take care of yourself.

36
00:03:18,091 --> 00:03:21,051
Worry about yourself, Chu.
You drink too much.

37
00:03:22,579 --> 00:03:23,419
Here.

38
00:03:23,868 --> 00:03:24,778
Thank you.

39
00:03:26,419 --> 00:03:27,371
Well...

40
00:03:30,464 --> 00:03:31,324
See you around.

41
00:03:31,461 --> 00:03:32,591
Take care.

42
00:03:36,550 --> 00:03:40,310
Okae was the daughter
of a shoe store owner

43
00:03:40,637 --> 00:03:42,177
that used to be at the corner.

44
00:03:42,274 --> 00:03:43,894
She used to be quite pretty.

45
00:03:46,060 --> 00:03:48,520
Even though she was born
and raised in Shinjuku,

46
00:03:48,841 --> 00:03:50,421
she was like a pure maiden,

47
00:03:50,863 --> 00:03:53,283
carrying a white parasol all the time.

48
00:03:53,666 --> 00:03:56,496
- She spoke like an upper-class lady.
- I don't like her.

49
00:03:56,966 --> 00:03:58,846
She sounds like a pretentious girl.

50
00:03:58,965 --> 00:04:02,599
I knew some girls like that.
They don't know who they really are.

51
00:04:02,599 --> 00:04:05,149
We can't befriend such a girl.

52
00:04:06,629 --> 00:04:10,179
Chu, she was your first love, huh?

53
00:04:10,568 --> 00:04:11,858
Stop it.

54
00:04:12,711 --> 00:04:13,921
You have the wrong idea.

55
00:04:15,609 --> 00:04:16,609
And then...

56
00:04:17,353 --> 00:04:19,933
she was discovered
by a famous movie director,

57
00:04:20,403 --> 00:04:22,443
but her acting career wasn't successful.

58
00:04:23,106 --> 00:04:24,106
Later on,

59
00:04:24,973 --> 00:04:28,183
she married some rich guy.
That's what I heard.

60
00:04:28,369 --> 00:04:31,669
She doesn't look rich, does she?

61
00:04:32,345 --> 00:04:34,555
I bet the story is made up.

62
00:04:35,004 --> 00:04:36,504
That's why I don't like women.

63
00:04:37,717 --> 00:04:40,113
To be honest,
I don't know if it's true or not.

64
00:04:40,422 --> 00:04:43,382
Besides, we hadn't seen each other
for almost four decades.

65
00:04:44,926 --> 00:04:47,488
She seems to make a hard living.

66
00:04:47,816 --> 00:04:51,714
Then you don't really know
about her life for those years?

67
00:04:52,269 --> 00:04:54,689
She came back to this area recently.

68
00:04:55,641 --> 00:04:58,191
At first, I didn't even recognize her.

69
00:04:59,322 --> 00:05:02,440
Their croquettes are great.
Eat it while they're still hot.

70
00:05:02,440 --> 00:05:04,320
Eat it as soon as you get home. Okay?

71
00:05:05,305 --> 00:05:07,595
Or would you like to eat it now?

72
00:05:08,423 --> 00:05:09,433
Yes?

73
00:05:10,894 --> 00:05:11,854
Here you...

74
00:05:20,993 --> 00:05:22,163
Chu?

75
00:05:25,875 --> 00:05:26,875
It is you.

76
00:05:27,606 --> 00:05:28,856
Chu, right?

77
00:05:29,800 --> 00:05:30,630
What?

78
00:05:31,779 --> 00:05:34,579
It's Kae, from the shoe store.

79
00:05:38,489 --> 00:05:39,449
Okae?

80
00:05:40,377 --> 00:05:41,747
Long time, no see.

81
00:05:42,197 --> 00:05:43,237
How have you been?

82
00:05:45,044 --> 00:05:46,504
Had some ups and downs...

83
00:05:47,352 --> 00:05:50,482
but I'm okay, as you can see.

84
00:05:51,818 --> 00:05:53,198
See you soon.

85
00:05:55,288 --> 00:05:56,338
Teppei.

86
00:05:56,622 --> 00:05:57,792
Wait.

87
00:06:04,260 --> 00:06:05,420
I'm what?

88
00:06:05,574 --> 00:06:07,654
Lavishing money on a young lover?

89
00:06:10,957 --> 00:06:13,997
Chu's losing his mind, isn't he?

90
00:06:14,131 --> 00:06:15,341
I hope he's okay.

91
00:06:17,069 --> 00:06:18,819
But he is not completely...

92
00:06:19,535 --> 00:06:21,825
wrong about it.

93
00:06:24,551 --> 00:06:28,811
That young man is the only son
of Kae's brother.

94
00:06:29,264 --> 00:06:31,496
She saw him at
her brother's funeral last year,

95
00:06:31,642 --> 00:06:34,432
for the first time in more than ten years.

96
00:06:56,403 --> 00:06:57,323
So...

97
00:06:58,043 --> 00:07:00,417
do you have the money
to cover the service?

98
00:07:00,417 --> 00:07:01,497
Of course, not.

99
00:07:02,682 --> 00:07:03,722
No?

100
00:07:04,508 --> 00:07:06,427
The body's been cremated.

101
00:07:06,429 --> 00:07:08,059
That's why I called you, Auntie.

102
00:07:08,762 --> 00:07:11,182
For money? I don't have any either.

103
00:07:13,954 --> 00:07:15,124
Then we'll have to run.

104
00:07:15,625 --> 00:07:17,795
How can you run away?

105
00:07:18,277 --> 00:07:21,370
- What about the ashes?
- I don't care.

106
00:07:21,371 --> 00:07:24,626
Come on. He's your father.

107
00:07:24,626 --> 00:07:27,006
That asshole? He is no one to me.

108
00:07:27,445 --> 00:07:30,939
I was relieved when he disappeared
without a trace. Then he died.

109
00:07:30,940 --> 00:07:33,880
It's not even worth picking up his bones.

110
00:07:34,199 --> 00:07:35,159
Listen here.

111
00:07:35,668 --> 00:07:38,378
No matter how terrible he was,
he's still your father.

112
00:07:38,755 --> 00:07:40,295
Blood is thicker than water.

113
00:07:40,910 --> 00:07:43,250
You can't ignore it.

114
00:07:43,676 --> 00:07:46,096
And you know it.
That's why you called me.

115
00:07:52,474 --> 00:07:55,144
You are hopeless.

116
00:07:55,507 --> 00:07:58,517
I'll ask them to see
if you can pay in installments.

117
00:08:00,689 --> 00:08:02,069
Unfortunately,

118
00:08:02,529 --> 00:08:03,949
Kae's nephew is a bum,

119
00:08:04,526 --> 00:08:06,816
just like his father.

120
00:08:07,404 --> 00:08:08,944
His wife left him.

121
00:08:09,437 --> 00:08:12,907
He has no job, and he's in his 40s.

122
00:08:16,050 --> 00:08:17,590
I'm home.

123
00:08:18,026 --> 00:08:19,026
Teppei,

124
00:08:19,708 --> 00:08:21,128
have you eaten dinner?

125
00:08:31,902 --> 00:08:34,372
What a mess!

126
00:08:39,936 --> 00:08:40,896
Shut up.

127
00:08:46,534 --> 00:08:49,164
You are so sloppy.

128
00:09:01,137 --> 00:09:02,517
Hey, Nguyen, come here.

129
00:09:03,835 --> 00:09:04,875
Get the other side.

130
00:09:06,880 --> 00:09:07,840
Ready?

131
00:09:08,465 --> 00:09:09,925
Grip the ends.

132
00:09:11,343 --> 00:09:12,253
Okay.

133
00:09:28,938 --> 00:09:29,858
Here you go.

134
00:09:37,734 --> 00:09:39,524
You like it? Delicious, isn't it?

135
00:09:41,836 --> 00:09:45,546
I've wanted to feed you
this hot pot for one for a while.

136
00:09:47,589 --> 00:09:49,549
But it's not "hot pot for one,"

137
00:09:50,048 --> 00:09:51,888
if the two of us eat it together.

138
00:09:53,552 --> 00:09:54,392
Okae.

139
00:09:54,720 --> 00:09:56,554
- Want some?
- Sorry.

140
00:09:56,555 --> 00:09:58,305
I have to go back to work.

141
00:09:58,890 --> 00:10:00,520
The part-timer quit.

142
00:10:01,680 --> 00:10:04,520
These days, young folks don't know
what hard work means.

143
00:10:05,206 --> 00:10:08,256
Why don't you ask
your nephew to help you?

144
00:10:08,679 --> 00:10:11,009
- You agree?
- Stop your nonsense.

145
00:10:12,894 --> 00:10:13,934
Where are you going?

146
00:10:14,531 --> 00:10:16,201
I finished it, so don't complain.

147
00:10:16,621 --> 00:10:17,911
Can I borrow some money?

148
00:10:18,822 --> 00:10:20,492
Going out for a drink again?

149
00:10:20,972 --> 00:10:23,552
I lent you money the other day.

150
00:10:24,248 --> 00:10:25,088
Fine.

151
00:10:25,542 --> 00:10:26,422
Wait.

152
00:10:26,934 --> 00:10:28,854
You give me no choice.

153
00:10:33,413 --> 00:10:35,953
You don't have a job?

154
00:10:37,554 --> 00:10:39,134
No job and you just get drunk?

155
00:10:39,559 --> 00:10:41,229
Don't you even want to help her?

156
00:10:41,651 --> 00:10:43,307
Hey, cut it out.

157
00:10:43,609 --> 00:10:46,189
Don't worry about me.

158
00:10:50,465 --> 00:10:52,034
What have you done?

159
00:10:52,217 --> 00:10:55,967
He's struggling to figure out
how to go on with his life.

160
00:10:56,156 --> 00:10:57,786
Why can't he have a drink?

161
00:10:58,162 --> 00:11:00,212
Just mind your own business.

162
00:11:00,644 --> 00:11:01,894
Master, check please.

163
00:11:03,371 --> 00:11:04,631
Twelve hundred yen.

164
00:11:08,274 --> 00:11:09,234
Thank you.

165
00:11:15,717 --> 00:11:18,507
Should I have said nothing?

166
00:11:21,186 --> 00:11:22,806
You are her childhood friend.

167
00:11:23,934 --> 00:11:25,974
That wasn't so out of line for you.

168
00:11:27,354 --> 00:11:28,514
First loves...

169
00:11:28,970 --> 00:11:30,390
never work out.

170
00:11:31,011 --> 00:11:33,261
Right?

171
00:11:36,545 --> 00:11:39,595
Wait for me, Teppei. Look.

172
00:11:40,330 --> 00:11:42,870
I circled the good ones.

173
00:11:43,826 --> 00:11:44,746
Look.

174
00:11:47,415 --> 00:11:48,455
Auntie,

175
00:11:48,940 --> 00:11:52,480
do you think that a man who filed
for bankruptcy can find a good job?

176
00:11:52,980 --> 00:11:56,393
There are a lot of jobs
if you keep your expectations realistic.

177
00:11:56,598 --> 00:11:59,221
What he said may be a good idea.
The no-tell motel.

178
00:11:59,386 --> 00:12:01,556
I can ask the manager for you.

179
00:12:01,793 --> 00:12:02,713
Come on.

180
00:12:02,931 --> 00:12:04,521
I'm still young.

181
00:12:04,998 --> 00:12:07,708
Unlike you,
I can't give up on my future yet.

182
00:12:12,247 --> 00:12:15,127
Then... what do you want to do?

183
00:12:18,144 --> 00:12:19,224
I was like you once.

184
00:12:19,528 --> 00:12:20,738
When I was young,

185
00:12:21,157 --> 00:12:24,577
I chased after something fancy.

186
00:12:25,495 --> 00:12:27,915
A luxurious life that everyone would envy.

187
00:12:29,338 --> 00:12:30,298
But...

188
00:12:31,167 --> 00:12:33,587
I found nothing in my hand

189
00:12:34,293 --> 00:12:36,583
when I thought that I finally got it.

190
00:12:42,596 --> 00:12:46,136
I know you have to learn
from your own failures.

191
00:12:48,825 --> 00:12:49,955
Get a drink, okay?

192
00:12:52,920 --> 00:12:54,210
Come home safely.

193
00:13:16,775 --> 00:13:17,855
Teppei?

194
00:13:18,673 --> 00:13:19,963
Wake up.

195
00:13:20,675 --> 00:13:22,345
Regarding the job,

196
00:13:23,053 --> 00:13:24,763
my manager wants to interview...

197
00:13:46,857 --> 00:13:47,817
Hey, Chu.

198
00:13:48,328 --> 00:13:50,311
Did you lose at the horse races again?

199
00:13:50,497 --> 00:13:51,707
No.

200
00:13:53,249 --> 00:13:54,919
Remember Kae's nephew?

201
00:13:55,829 --> 00:13:58,290
He took everything,
including credit cards,

202
00:13:58,291 --> 00:14:01,171
her ATM card, cash, and ran away.

203
00:14:02,685 --> 00:14:04,985
Okae shouldn't have spoiled him.

204
00:14:05,470 --> 00:14:07,100
But still...

205
00:14:14,980 --> 00:14:16,480
Good evening.

206
00:14:16,815 --> 00:14:17,775
Welcome.

207
00:14:18,873 --> 00:14:21,293
Give me warm sake and the hot pot.

208
00:14:21,653 --> 00:14:24,193
Kae, did something good happen?

209
00:14:28,201 --> 00:14:29,251
Look at this.

210
00:14:29,995 --> 00:14:31,075
Isn't it pretty?

211
00:14:32,564 --> 00:14:35,734
Teppei sent it to me

212
00:14:36,107 --> 00:14:37,991
as a birthday gift.

213
00:14:39,076 --> 00:14:40,379
It looks great on you.

214
00:14:40,380 --> 00:14:41,659
Doesn't it?

215
00:14:41,660 --> 00:14:43,990
I was right.
Blood is thicker than water.

216
00:14:45,301 --> 00:14:47,811
Did you get your money back?

217
00:14:48,226 --> 00:14:51,874
I don't care about that anymore.

218
00:15:03,650 --> 00:15:04,610
Okae,

219
00:15:05,336 --> 00:15:06,926
you disappoint me.

220
00:15:07,782 --> 00:15:08,742
Why?

221
00:15:09,051 --> 00:15:10,761
You're deceived by such a gift.

222
00:15:11,500 --> 00:15:14,130
I'm sure he bought it with your money.

223
00:15:15,263 --> 00:15:17,042
I'm telling you,

224
00:15:17,043 --> 00:15:19,870
it's not about the money.

225
00:15:19,870 --> 00:15:21,490
What's wrong with you?

226
00:15:22,088 --> 00:15:23,258
Wake up.

227
00:15:24,090 --> 00:15:25,430
When you were young,

228
00:15:25,842 --> 00:15:27,932
you were beautiful and independent.

229
00:15:28,297 --> 00:15:30,217
You were an awesome lady.

230
00:15:31,084 --> 00:15:35,173
Are you saying
that I'm embarrassing now?

231
00:15:35,173 --> 00:15:36,463
Yes, you're embarrassing.

232
00:15:37,145 --> 00:15:39,446
He's the only family you have?
So, what?

233
00:15:39,447 --> 00:15:40,787
You're being irrational.

234
00:15:41,941 --> 00:15:43,531
You have no idea.

235
00:15:44,071 --> 00:15:47,121
Once I started living with Teppei,
I learned it was a joy

236
00:15:47,652 --> 00:15:51,032
to work for someone else
for the first time in my life.

237
00:15:51,521 --> 00:15:53,021
I should be thanking him.

238
00:15:53,481 --> 00:15:55,788
Okae, are you being serious?

239
00:15:55,788 --> 00:15:59,267
Yeah, I'm serious. Completely serious.

240
00:16:01,039 --> 00:16:02,999
How can you criticize me?

241
00:16:03,868 --> 00:16:05,288
You have no family.

242
00:16:05,792 --> 00:16:08,302
You get drunk by yourself every night.

243
00:16:08,729 --> 00:16:11,359
You're more embarrassing than I am.

244
00:16:20,086 --> 00:16:21,246
Here you go.

245
00:16:22,357 --> 00:16:23,277
Enjoy.

246
00:16:39,916 --> 00:16:40,916
I'm sorry.

247
00:16:41,808 --> 00:16:42,757
I was too harsh.

248
00:16:49,926 --> 00:16:51,096
Have some.

249
00:16:52,027 --> 00:16:53,117
No thanks.

250
00:16:55,687 --> 00:16:57,647
Just eat it.

251
00:17:14,012 --> 00:17:15,472
So, you like it?

252
00:17:24,366 --> 00:17:27,076
Later, I can make rice porridge
with the soup for you.

253
00:17:28,423 --> 00:17:29,423
Good idea!

254
00:17:43,104 --> 00:17:44,064
Hello?

255
00:17:47,879 --> 00:17:48,709
Yes.

256
00:17:57,459 --> 00:17:58,469
I understand.

257
00:18:02,207 --> 00:18:03,837
Teppei was arrested.

258
00:18:18,329 --> 00:18:19,959
Kae's nephew was charged

259
00:18:20,328 --> 00:18:22,882
with several offenses,
including theft,

260
00:18:23,311 --> 00:18:24,901
swindling on small loans,

261
00:18:25,480 --> 00:18:27,553
and more.

262
00:18:27,982 --> 00:18:29,572
He got a prison sentence.

263
00:18:30,068 --> 00:18:33,698
Now Kae visits him in prison often.
That's what I heard.

264
00:18:38,855 --> 00:18:42,275
About six months have passed
since then.

265
00:18:48,002 --> 00:18:50,672
- Good evening.
- Welcome.

266
00:18:51,464 --> 00:18:52,834
Have a seat there.

267
00:18:53,613 --> 00:18:56,573
Master, make him anything he wants.

268
00:18:57,053 --> 00:18:58,673
Kae, who is this?

269
00:18:59,180 --> 00:19:02,100
This is Teppei's son.
His name is Shohei.

270
00:19:03,893 --> 00:19:07,223
I didn't know that
Teppei had such a big boy.

271
00:19:07,939 --> 00:19:11,649
Since his mother got remarried,
he has no place to stay.

272
00:19:12,040 --> 00:19:14,250
So, I took custody of him.

273
00:19:14,922 --> 00:19:15,922
Man,

274
00:19:16,463 --> 00:19:18,253
what a nuisance, huh?

275
00:19:19,284 --> 00:19:20,864
What would you like?

276
00:19:21,744 --> 00:19:22,574
Meat!

277
00:19:24,380 --> 00:19:26,850
- And you, Kae? Hot pot for one?
- Nothing for me.

278
00:19:27,137 --> 00:19:29,347
We ate hot pot at home
last night together.

279
00:19:31,713 --> 00:19:32,793
Wait. Warm sake.

280
00:19:33,631 --> 00:19:34,551
Sure.

281
00:19:45,569 --> 00:19:48,397
Here you go.
A special plate full of meat.

282
00:19:51,130 --> 00:19:53,130
- Let's eat.
- Go ahead.

283
00:19:58,227 --> 00:19:59,187
Hey.

284
00:19:59,511 --> 00:20:02,391
Make sure you chew it well.

285
00:20:07,701 --> 00:20:10,121
- Master, give him some juice.
- Sure.

286
00:20:16,682 --> 00:20:18,142
I never imagined...

287
00:20:19,241 --> 00:20:20,451
I'd have the chance...

288
00:20:21,030 --> 00:20:23,900
to raise a kid at this age.

289
00:20:37,286 --> 00:20:38,416
Okae...

290
00:20:39,170 --> 00:20:41,460
never looked at her feet,
under her nose,

291
00:20:41,949 --> 00:20:44,329
even though she was
a shoe store's daughter.

292
00:20:46,371 --> 00:20:48,121
I just guess...

293
00:20:49,071 --> 00:20:52,201
that she wanted to see other scenaries.

294
00:20:55,088 --> 00:20:56,168
You're right.

295
00:20:58,299 --> 00:20:59,929
That's what she wanted.

296
00:21:01,844 --> 00:21:05,094
Tonight, she looked even better

297
00:21:05,628 --> 00:21:06,918
than when she was young.

298
00:21:10,418 --> 00:21:11,328
Chu,

299
00:21:12,485 --> 00:21:14,115
this one's on me.

300
00:21:18,694 --> 00:21:19,654
Are you sure?

301
00:21:53,114 --> 00:21:54,984
It's not easy to live one's life,

302
00:21:55,629 --> 00:21:58,209
whether you're alone
or have someone else.

303
00:22:02,528 --> 00:22:03,488
That's good.

304
00:22:03,904 --> 00:22:05,444
In an earthen pot for one,

305
00:22:05,864 --> 00:22:07,967
simmer Chinese cabbage,

306
00:22:07,967 --> 00:22:10,477
pork and enoki mushrooms
in a bonito broth.

307
00:22:10,895 --> 00:22:12,445
That's all there is to it.

308
00:22:13,840 --> 00:22:15,880
Simple is the best.

309
00:22:18,129 --> 00:22:20,339
It looks delicious.

310
00:22:24,283 --> 00:22:25,493
Hold it, Kae.

311
00:22:26,384 --> 00:22:28,004
Don't forget the bushukan.

312
00:22:29,015 --> 00:22:31,725
That's very important.

313
00:22:33,292 --> 00:22:36,092
Bushukan is a citrus fruit from Tosa.

314
00:22:36,466 --> 00:22:39,886
The juice is a perfect match
for my hot pot.

315
00:22:41,358 --> 00:22:42,778
Make sure to eat a lot.

316
00:22:48,826 --> 00:22:51,536
- It's so delicious.
- Isn't it?

317
00:23:41,039 --> 00:23:46,044
THIS STORY IS FICTION

